title: [PODFIC] An Everyday Kindness
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2Fk617K

by mintsinthemug

“What is that?” Bucky asks softly.

“Snow,” Steve says. The word lodges in his throat, making him cough. “It was…” He swallows. “That’s what I saw when the Valkyrie was going down.” He’s trembling. He clasps his hands on the desk to keep them still.

“You said you got the white for me. Because of the train.” Bucky sounds puzzled.

Without the drawing in his immediate line of sight Steve’s able to wrench his eyes towards the window, then flinches when he sees the snow covering everything. It’s New York, he thinks. It’s New York and you’re inside and warm and you’re not frozen and you’re not going to die. “It was. Just, not all of it. I’m sorry. I didn't—”

Bucky’s incredulous snort cuts him off. “Are you apologizing for the train not being your biggest fucking trauma for once?”

 
Podfic of Taste_Is_Sweet’s ‘An Everyday Kindness’.

blog.name: over-canon-watch
blog.title: Headcanon Central [27]
blog.description: \\ Marvel and Overwatch requests // my work is always genderneutral unless specified & none of the images used for this blog belong to me

body:
Accidentally Calling Star-Lord ‘Dad’ (2)

for @silverquartx <3

Part 1: https://over-canon-watch.tumblr.com/post/181750537970

  • Peter didn’t bother to clear up the mess he’d made - instead, his main focus was getting back to you before you could fly off without him,
  • He rushed back to find Milano parked in the same place he left it, engines off and doors shut.
  • As he stepped aboard, he found you sat in your regular seat, headphones on and your own mixtape bleeding through them - it had been a gift from Quill when you let it slip that your birthday was coming up.
  • You had expected to find the other guardians aboard, so you were relieved that you could have a little peace as you were in no mood to talk.
  • He saw you sitting there and staring off into space, his heart tugged a little as you looked embarrassed.
  • So, he thought it best to leave you alone and just fly you back without hassle.
  • The second you landed, he saw you bolt for the exit without a word.
  • Being the crafty guy he was, he locked the doors before you had the chance to escape
  • “Dude!” You raised your voice and looked back at him, a what the hell expression on your face.
  • “You’re not leaving until we talk this out because clearly, it’s going to be awkward if we don’t.”
  • “You’re the one who’s making awkward right now, old man.”
  • He held his hand to his chest, “Y/N, I’m wounded.”
  • You tried not to laugh but you couldn’t help it.
  • Immediately, the mood lightened as the both of you dissolved into laughter.
  • Peter took a step towards you, he ruffled your hair lightly and smiled at you.
  • Without thinking, you latched your arms around his body and sighed. He held you there naturally as if he was protecting you from the world.
  • It was like everything seemed to fall into place from there on.
